1002/mds.25629","container-title":"Movement Disorders","abstract":"Background Although essential tremor (ET) is among the most prevalent neurological diseases, its precise pathogenesis is not understood. Purkinje cell loss has been observed in some studies and is the focus of interest and debate. Expressing these data as Purkinje cells/layer length allows one to adjust for the inherent curved nature of the cerebellar folia. Capitalizing on the Essential Tremor Centralized Brain Repository, we quantified Purkinje cell linear density in cases vs. controls.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Louis","given":"Elan D.","literal":""},{"family":"Louis","given":"Elan D.","literal":""},{"family":"Babij","given":"Rachel","literal":""},{"family":"Babij","given":"Rachel","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Michelle","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Michelle","literal":""},{"family":"Cortés","given":"Etty","literal":""},{"family":"Cortes","given":"Etty","literal":""},{"family":"Vonsattel","given":"Jean Paul","literal":""},{"family":"Vonsattel","given":"Jean-Paul G.","literal":""}],"citation-key":"louis_quantification_2013","year":"2013","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Quantification of cerebellar hemispheric purkinje cell linear density: 32 ET cases versus 16 controls."],"author-links":["[[Author/Elan D. Louis]]","[[Author/Elan D. Louis]]","[[Author/Rachel Babij]]","[[Author/Rachel Babij]]","[[Author/Michelle Lee]]","[[Author/Michelle Lee]]","[[Author/Etty Cortés]]","[[Author/Etty Cortes]]","[[Author/Jean Paul Vonsattel]]","[[Author/Jean-Paul G. Vonsattel]]"],"attachment":[],"related":[[]]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"last_embed":{"hash":"1ulz9z9","at":1774951888795}},"smart_blocks:Research/@louis_quantification_2013.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.01203819,-0.07138135,0.00886376,-0.03594428,-0.04994561,0.06040167,0.01872408,0.08201838,0.03580007,0.